 # to sort an array
fruits=["Lemon", "Orange", "Apple", "Watermelon"]
fruits.sort()
print("The sorted array is:\n")
for i in fruits:
     print(i, end= " ")
fruits.sort(reverse=True)
print("\nThe array sorted in reverse order is:\n")
for i in fruits:
    print(i, end=" ")
    
 
*********OUTPUT********

The sorted array is:
Apple Lemon Orange Watermelon 

The array sorted in reverse order is:
Watermelon Orange Lemon Apple 
